        "description": {
          "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> The bloodbrother has a Large or smaller creature @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.kWc1fhmv9LBiTuei]{Grabbed} or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.VcDeM8A5oI6VqhbM]{Restrained} with their bone spur</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The bloodbrother tries to imprison the required creature in their ribcage prison. The bloodbrother attempts an Athletics check against the creature's Reflex DC, imprisoning it on a success. The bloodbrother's bone spur is no longer grabbing or restraining the creature they've imprisoned, so the bloodbrother is free to use their bone spur Strike once again. The bloodbrother can't attack a creature they've imprisoned and can have only one creature imprisoned in their ribcage prison at a time. An imprisoned creature is restrained ([[/act escape dc=25]]) and temporarily immune to the bloodbrother's frigid touch while restrained.</p>",
